        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 24 at 2:29PM MDT until August 24 at 3:00PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>SVRBOU

The National Weather Service in Denver has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Northeastern Lincoln County in east central Colorado...

* Until 300 PM MDT.

* At 229 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 6 miles northeast
of Arriba, or 27 miles east of Limon, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

* Locations impacted include...
Arriba.
</description>
        <instruction>Anyone outdoors should move to shelter inside a well-built structure
and stay away from windows. This storm is capable of producing
dangerous hail.</instruction>
